04:51.909 --> 04:53.858
Oh, she's a she?

04:53.961 --> 04:55.460
Yes, obviously, just

04:55.529 --> 04:57.296
didn't want to name her, 'cause
that would've been creepy.

04:57.364 --> 05:00.048
-Of course.
-All right, come on,
give it a go, come on.

05:00.167 --> 05:02.334
Oh, yeah, listen, no,
it's, like, super nice

05:02.419 --> 05:04.503
of you to show me the ropes and
everything, but I'm actually not

05:04.588 --> 05:06.037
gonna be working here
that long. You know,

05:06.173 --> 05:07.372
it's kind of
a temporary thing for me.

05:07.474 --> 05:08.840
Okay, don't
look at it like that,

05:08.926 --> 05:10.175
because you might
actually be good at this.

05:10.311 --> 05:11.426
Uh-huh. Yeah, I just think

05:11.512 --> 05:12.844
this might be
a waste of your time.

05:12.980 --> 05:14.379
Don't be afraid to succeed.

05:14.481 --> 05:16.682
Come on, step on up.

05:16.767 --> 05:19.184
-Okay.
-Okay.

05:19.320 --> 05:20.936
We gonna take this,
put that in your hand,

05:21.021 --> 05:22.721
because you're gonna
catch the meat.

05:22.856 --> 05:24.523
All right.

05:24.608 --> 05:26.441
That there? Okay.

05:26.527 --> 05:28.443
The best piece of advice
I can give you--

05:28.529 --> 05:30.996
never ask the customers
how thin they want it.

05:31.064 --> 05:33.198
You do not want to deal
with the politics.

05:33.283 --> 05:34.866
All right, now.

05:35.002 --> 05:37.569
There you go,
let it fall nicely.

05:37.671 --> 05:40.122
All right, all about the meat.

05:40.207 --> 05:42.424
It's all in the shoulders, girl.

05:42.543 --> 05:44.376
But you keep practicing, okay?
You got this.

05:44.461 --> 05:46.044
Okay.

05:46.130 --> 05:47.879
(whispering): Sam! Sammy.

05:47.965 --> 05:50.349
Get out! Abort!

05:50.417 --> 05:51.249
What?

05:51.385 --> 05:53.084
What are you doing?

05:53.187 --> 05:55.270
No way-- sam!
What's up?

05:58.392 --> 06:00.525
-It-it's been a minute.
-You're not wrong. (chuckles)

06:00.611 --> 06:02.260
yeah, brit told me
you were back in town.

06:02.396 --> 06:04.396
I was gonna call you, but, uh...

06:04.481 --> 06:06.531
(clears throat)

06:06.617 --> 06:08.367
I-I didn't.

06:08.435 --> 06:10.369
Hell... Hey, sam.

06:10.437 --> 06:12.738
Hey.

06:12.873 --> 06:15.207
It's great to see you guys.

06:15.275 --> 06:17.108
Yeah. No, we were just,
we were just...

06:17.244 --> 06:19.077
We were, uh, grocery shopping
and... (laughs)

06:19.213 --> 06:21.046
I know that sounds obvious.

06:21.114 --> 06:23.215
But, um... This is great.

06:23.283 --> 06:24.716
This is great.

06:24.785 --> 06:26.001
You got a job.

06:26.086 --> 06:27.586
And at giovanni's.
I mean...

06:27.671 --> 06:29.171
Such good produce.

06:29.256 --> 06:30.806
Really, really good, impressive.

06:30.924 --> 06:32.724
Yeah, but she's just
volunteering.

06:32.793 --> 06:35.394
She usually helps the elderly
with their groceries and such.

06:35.462 --> 06:37.229
But I'm sure she could
help you out just this once.

06:37.297 --> 06:39.014
-At a meat counter?
-Felicia, it's fine.

06:39.099 --> 06:40.766
Not just at
the meat counter, brit.

06:40.901 --> 06:42.901
She's in all different
departments, right?

06:42.969 --> 06:44.302
I just, I work here, that's it.

06:44.438 --> 06:45.637
I work here, you know?

06:45.773 --> 06:46.772
This is my hairnet.

06:46.857 --> 06:49.274
What? Since when?
(laughs)

06:49.410 --> 06:52.277
I can never
keep up with her, right?

06:52.413 --> 06:54.813
I'm gonna leave you to it.

06:54.915 --> 06:56.615
(chuckles)

06:57.668 --> 06:59.618
(joel clears his throat)

06:59.753 --> 07:02.153
-so, uh, can we order something?
Or we don't have to...
-Oh, yeah. Mm-hmm.

07:02.289 --> 07:03.955
-Sure.
-Cool, uh,

07:04.041 --> 07:05.791
half a pound of that
turkey pastrami, please.

07:07.294 --> 07:10.128
Uh, how's your dad's
contracting business going?

07:10.214 --> 07:12.464
Uh, you know what, it's actually
joel's business now.

07:12.599 --> 07:15.166
-Huh.
-Yeah, my dad had
to have his hips replaced,

07:15.302 --> 07:16.685
so I'm pretty lucky.

07:17.971 --> 07:19.504
It's, um...

07:19.640 --> 07:21.440
It's a little more
than half a pound.

07:21.525 --> 07:23.225
